72InternalDataChannelInit::InternalDataChannelInit(const DataChannelInit& base)
73 : DataChannelInit(base), open_handshake_role(kOpener) {
74 // If the channel is externally negotiated, do not send the OPEN message.
75 if (base.negotiated) {
76 open_handshake_role = kNone;
77 } else {
78 // Datachannel is externally negotiated. Ignore the id value.
79 // Specified in createDataChannel, WebRTC spec section 6.1 bullet 13.
80 id = -1;
81 }
82 // Backwards compatibility: If maxRetransmits or maxRetransmitTime
83 // are negative, the feature is not enabled.
84 // Values are clamped to a 16bit range.
85 if (maxRetransmits) {
86 if (*maxRetransmits < 0) {
87 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
88 << "Accepting maxRetransmits < 0 for backwards compatibility";
89 maxRetransmits = absl::nullopt;
90 } else if (*maxRetransmits > std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
91 maxRetransmits = std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
92 }
93 }
94
95 if (maxRetransmitTime) {
96 if (*maxRetransmitTime < 0) {
97 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
98 << "Accepting maxRetransmitTime < 0 for backwards compatibility";
99 maxRetransmitTime = absl::nullopt;
100 } else if (*maxRetransmitTime > std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
101 maxRetransmitTime = std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
102 }
103 }
104}

106bool SctpSidAllocator::AllocateSid(rtc::SSLRole role, int* sid) {
107 int potential_sid = (role == rtc::SSL_CLIENT) ? 0 : 1;
108 while (!IsSidAvailable(potential_sid)) {
109 potential_sid += 2;
110 if (potential_sid > static_cast<int>(cricket::kMaxSctpSid)) {
111 return false;
112 }
113 }
114
115 *sid = potential_sid;
116 used_sids_.insert(potential_sid);
117 return true;
118}
119
120bool SctpSidAllocator::ReserveSid(int sid) {
121 if (!IsSidAvailable(sid)) {
122 return false;
123 }
124 used_sids_.insert(sid);
125 return true;
126}
127
128void SctpSidAllocator::ReleaseSid(int sid) {
129 auto it = used_sids_.find(sid);
130 if (it != used_sids_.end()) {
131 used_sids_.erase(it);
132 }
133}
134
135bool SctpSidAllocator::IsSidAvailable(int sid) const {
136 if (sid < static_cast<int>(cricket::kMinSctpSid) ||
137 sid > static_cast<int>(cricket::kMaxSctpSid)) {
138 return false;
139 }
140 return used_sids_.find(sid) == used_sids_.end();
141}

143rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel> SctpDataChannel::Create(
144 SctpDataChannelProviderInterface* provider,
145 const std::string& label,
146 const InternalDataChannelInit& config,
147 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
148 rtc::Thread* network_thread) {
149 auto channel = rtc::make_ref_counted<SctpDataChannel>(
150 config, provider, label, signaling_thread, network_thread);
151 if (!channel->Init()) {
152 return nullptr;
153 }
154 return channel;
155}

157// static
158rtc::scoped_refptr<DataChannelInterface> SctpDataChannel::CreateProxy(
159 rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel> channel) {
160 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11547): incorporate the network thread in the proxy.
161 // Also, consider allowing the proxy object to own the reference (std::move).
162 // As is, the proxy has a raw pointer and no reference to the channel object
163 // and trusting that the lifetime management aligns with the
164 // sctp_data_channels_ array in SctpDataChannelController.
165 return DataChannelProxy::Create(channel->signaling_thread_, channel.get());
166}

168SctpDataChannel::SctpDataChannel(const InternalDataChannelInit& config,
169 SctpDataChannelProviderInterface* provider,
170 const std::string& label,
171 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
172 rtc::Thread* network_thread)
173 : signaling_thread_(signaling_thread),
174 network_thread_(network_thread),
175 internal_id_(GenerateUniqueId()),
176 label_(label),
177 config_(config),
178 observer_(nullptr),
179 provider_(provider) {
180 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
181}

183bool SctpDataChannel::Init() {
184 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
185 if (config_.id < -1 ||
186 (config_.maxRetransmits && *config_.maxRetransmits < 0) ||
187 (config_.maxRetransmitTime && *config_.maxRetransmitTime < 0)) {
188 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to initialize the SCTP data channel due to "
189 "invalid DataChannelInit.";
190 return false;
191 }
192 if (config_.maxRetransmits && config_.maxRetransmitTime) {
193 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
194 << "maxRetransmits and maxRetransmitTime should not be both set.";
195 return false;
196 }
197
198 switch (config_.open_handshake_role) {
199 case webrtc::InternalDataChannelInit::kNone: // pre-negotiated
200 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeReady;
201 break;
202 case webrtc::InternalDataChannelInit::kOpener:
203 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeShouldSendOpen;
204 break;
205 case webrtc::InternalDataChannelInit::kAcker:
206 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeShouldSendAck;
207 break;
208 }
209
210 // Try to connect to the transport in case the transport channel already
211 // exists.
212 OnTransportChannelCreated();
213
214 // Checks if the transport is ready to send because the initial channel
215 // ready signal may have been sent before the DataChannel creation.
216 // This has to be done async because the upper layer objects (e.g.
217 // Chrome glue and WebKit) are not wired up properly until after this
218 // function returns.
219 if (provider_->ReadyToSendData()) {
220 AddRef();
221 rtc::Thread::Current()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
222 [this] {
223 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
224 if (state_ != kClosed)
225 OnTransportReady(true);
226 },
227 [this] { Release(); }));
228 }
229
230 return true;
231}
232
233SctpDataChannel::~SctpDataChannel() {
234 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
235}

237void SctpDataChannel::RegisterObserver(DataChannelObserver* observer) {
238 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
239 observer_ = observer;
240 DeliverQueuedReceivedData();
241}

243void SctpDataChannel::UnregisterObserver() {
244 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
245 observer_ = nullptr;
246}

248bool SctpDataChannel::reliable() const {
249 // May be called on any thread.
250 return !config_.maxRetransmits && !config_.maxRetransmitTime;
251}

254 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
255 return buffered_amount_;

258void SctpDataChannel::Close() {
259 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
260 if (state_ == kClosed)
261 return;
262 SetState(kClosing);
263 // Will send queued data before beginning the underlying closing procedure.
264 UpdateState();
265}

297bool SctpDataChannel::Send(const DataBuffer& buffer) {
298 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
299 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11547): Expect this method to be called on the network
300 // thread. Bring buffer management etc to the network thread and keep the
301 // operational state management on the signaling thread.
302
303 if (state_ != kOpen) {
304 return false;
305 }
306
307 buffered_amount_ += buffer.size();
308
309 // If the queue is non-empty, we're waiting for SignalReadyToSend,
310 // so just add to the end of the queue and keep waiting.
311 if (!queued_send_data_.Empty()) {
312 if (!QueueSendDataMessage(buffer)) {
313 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Closing the DataChannel due to a failure to queue "
314 "additional data.";
315 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#dom-rtcdatachannel-send step 5
316 // Note that the spec doesn't explicitly say to close in this situation.
317 CloseAbruptlyWithError(RTCError(RTCErrorType::RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED,
318 "Unable to queue data for sending"));
319 }
320 return true;
321 }
322
323 SendDataMessage(buffer, true);
324
325 // Always return true for SCTP DataChannel per the spec.
326 return true;
327}

329void SctpDataChannel::SetSctpSid(int sid) {
330 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
331 RTC_DCHECK_LT(config_.id, 0);
332 RTC_DCHECK_GE(sid, 0);
333 RTC_DCHECK_NE(handshake_state_, kHandshakeWaitingForAck);
334 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(state_, kConnecting);
335
336 if (config_.id == sid) {
337 return;
338 }
339
340 const_cast<InternalDataChannelInit&>(config_).id = sid;
341 provider_->AddSctpDataStream(sid);
342}
343
344void SctpDataChannel::OnClosingProcedureStartedRemotely(int sid) {
345 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
346 if (sid == config_.id && state_ != kClosing && state_ != kClosed) {
347 // Don't bother sending queued data since the side that initiated the
348 // closure wouldn't receive it anyway. See crbug.com/559394 for a lengthy
349 // discussion about this.
350 queued_send_data_.Clear();
351 queued_control_data_.Clear();
352 // Just need to change state to kClosing, SctpTransport will handle the
353 // rest of the closing procedure and OnClosingProcedureComplete will be
354 // called later.
355 started_closing_procedure_ = true;
356 SetState(kClosing);
357 }
358}
359
360void SctpDataChannel::OnClosingProcedureComplete(int sid) {
361 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
362 if (sid == config_.id) {
363 // If the closing procedure is complete, we should have finished sending
364 // all pending data and transitioned to kClosing already.
365 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(state_, kClosing);
366 RTC_DCHECK(queued_send_data_.Empty());
367 DisconnectFromProvider();
368 SetState(kClosed);
369 }
370}
371
372void SctpDataChannel::OnTransportChannelCreated() {
373 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
374 if (!connected_to_provider_) {
375 connected_to_provider_ = provider_->ConnectDataChannel(this);
376 }
377 // The sid may have been unassigned when provider_->ConnectDataChannel was
378 // done. So always add the streams even if connected_to_provider_ is true.
379 if (config_.id >= 0) {
380 provider_->AddSctpDataStream(config_.id);
381 }
382}
383
384void SctpDataChannel::OnTransportChannelClosed() {
385 // The SctpTransport is unusable (for example, because the SCTP m= section
386 // was rejected, or because the DTLS transport closed), so we need to close
387 // abruptly.
388 RTCError error = RTCError(RTCErrorType::OPERATION_ERROR_WITH_DATA,
389 "Transport channel closed");
390 error.set_error_detail(RTCErrorDetailType::SCTP_FAILURE);
391 CloseAbruptlyWithError(std::move(error));
392}

394DataChannelStats SctpDataChannel::GetStats() const {
395 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
396 DataChannelStats stats{internal_id_, id(), label(),
397 protocol(), state(), messages_sent(),
398 messages_received(), bytes_sent(), bytes_received()};
399 return stats;

402void SctpDataChannel::OnDataReceived(const cricket::ReceiveDataParams& params,
403 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& payload) {
404 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
405 if (params.sid != config_.id) {
406 return;
407 }
408
409 if (params.type == DataMessageType::kControl) {
410 if (handshake_state_ != kHandshakeWaitingForAck) {
411 // Ignore it if we are not expecting an ACK message.
412 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
413 << "DataChannel received unexpected CONTROL message, sid = "
414 << params.sid;
415 return;
416 }
417 if (ParseDataChannelOpenAckMessage(payload)) {
418 // We can send unordered as soon as we receive the ACK message.
419 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeReady;
420 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "DataChannel received OPEN_ACK message, sid = "
421 << params.sid;
422 } else {
423 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
424 << "DataChannel failed to parse OPEN_ACK message, sid = "
425 << params.sid;
426 }
427 return;
428 }
429
430 RTC_DCHECK(params.type == DataMessageType::kBinary ||
431 params.type == DataMessageType::kText);
432
433 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "DataChannel received DATA message, sid = "
434 << params.sid;
435 // We can send unordered as soon as we receive any DATA message since the
436 // remote side must have received the OPEN (and old clients do not send
437 // OPEN_ACK).
438 if (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeWaitingForAck) {
439 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeReady;
440 }
441
442 bool binary = (params.type == webrtc::DataMessageType::kBinary);
443 auto buffer = std::make_unique<DataBuffer>(payload, binary);
444 if (state_ == kOpen && observer_) {
445 ++messages_received_;
446 bytes_received_ += buffer->size();
447 observer_->OnMessage(*buffer.get());
448 } else {
449 if (queued_received_data_.byte_count() + payload.size() >
450 kMaxQueuedReceivedDataBytes) {
451 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Queued received data exceeds the max buffer size.";
452
453 queued_received_data_.Clear();
454 CloseAbruptlyWithError(
455 RTCError(RTCErrorType::RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED,
456 "Queued received data exceeds the max buffer size."));
457
458 return;
459 }
460 queued_received_data_.PushBack(std::move(buffer));
461 }
462}
463
464void SctpDataChannel::OnTransportReady(bool writable) {
465 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
466
467 writable_ = writable;
468 if (!writable) {
469 return;
470 }
471
472 SendQueuedControlMessages();
473 SendQueuedDataMessages();
474
475 UpdateState();
476}
477
478void SctpDataChannel::CloseAbruptlyWithError(RTCError error) {
479 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
480
481 if (state_ == kClosed) {
482 return;
483 }
484
485 if (connected_to_provider_) {
486 DisconnectFromProvider();
487 }
488
489 // Closing abruptly means any queued data gets thrown away.
490 buffered_amount_ = 0;
491
492 queued_send_data_.Clear();
493 queued_control_data_.Clear();
494
495 // Still go to "kClosing" before "kClosed", since observers may be expecting
496 // that.
497 SetState(kClosing);
498 error_ = std::move(error);
499 SetState(kClosed);
500}
501
502void SctpDataChannel::CloseAbruptlyWithDataChannelFailure(
503 const std::string& message) {
504 RTCError error(RTCErrorType::OPERATION_ERROR_WITH_DATA, message);
505 error.set_error_detail(RTCErrorDetailType::DATA_CHANNEL_FAILURE);
506 CloseAbruptlyWithError(std::move(error));
507}
508
509void SctpDataChannel::UpdateState() {
510 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
511 // UpdateState determines what to do from a few state variables. Include
512 // all conditions required for each state transition here for
513 // clarity. OnTransportReady(true) will send any queued data and then invoke
514 // UpdateState().
515
516 switch (state_) {
517 case kConnecting: {
518 if (connected_to_provider_) {
519 if (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeShouldSendOpen) {
520 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer payload;
521 WriteDataChannelOpenMessage(label_, config_, &payload);
522 SendControlMessage(payload);
523 } else if (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeShouldSendAck) {
524 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer payload;
525 WriteDataChannelOpenAckMessage(&payload);
526 SendControlMessage(payload);
527 }
528 if (writable_ && (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeReady ||
529 handshake_state_ == kHandshakeWaitingForAck)) {
530 SetState(kOpen);
531 // If we have received buffers before the channel got writable.
532 // Deliver them now.
533 DeliverQueuedReceivedData();
534 }
535 }
536 break;
537 }
538 case kOpen: {
539 break;
540 }
541 case kClosing: {
542 // Wait for all queued data to be sent before beginning the closing
543 // procedure.
544 if (queued_send_data_.Empty() && queued_control_data_.Empty()) {
545 // For SCTP data channels, we need to wait for the closing procedure
546 // to complete; after calling RemoveSctpDataStream,
547 // OnClosingProcedureComplete will end up called asynchronously
548 // afterwards.
549 if (connected_to_provider_ && !started_closing_procedure_ &&
550 config_.id >= 0) {
551 started_closing_procedure_ = true;
552 provider_->RemoveSctpDataStream(config_.id);
553 }
554 }
555 break;
556 }
557 case kClosed:
558 break;
559 }
560}
561
562void SctpDataChannel::SetState(DataState state) {
563 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
564 if (state_ == state) {
565 return;
566 }
567
568 state_ = state;
569 if (observer_) {
570 observer_->OnStateChange();
571 }
572 if (state_ == kOpen) {
573 SignalOpened(this);
574 } else if (state_ == kClosed) {
575 SignalClosed(this);
576 }
577}
578
579void SctpDataChannel::DisconnectFromProvider() {
580 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
581 if (!connected_to_provider_)
582 return;
583
584 provider_->DisconnectDataChannel(this);
585 connected_to_provider_ = false;
586}
587
588void SctpDataChannel::DeliverQueuedReceivedData() {
589 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
590 if (!observer_) {
591 return;
592 }
593
594 while (!queued_received_data_.Empty()) {
595 std::unique_ptr<DataBuffer> buffer = queued_received_data_.PopFront();
596 ++messages_received_;
597 bytes_received_ += buffer->size();
598 observer_->OnMessage(*buffer);
599 }
600}
601
602void SctpDataChannel::SendQueuedDataMessages() {
603 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
604 if (queued_send_data_.Empty()) {
605 return;
606 }
607
608 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == kOpen || state_ == kClosing);
609
610 while (!queued_send_data_.Empty()) {
611 std::unique_ptr<DataBuffer> buffer = queued_send_data_.PopFront();
612 if (!SendDataMessage(*buffer, false)) {
613 // Return the message to the front of the queue if sending is aborted.
614 queued_send_data_.PushFront(std::move(buffer));
615 break;
616 }
617 }
618}
619
620bool SctpDataChannel::SendDataMessage(const DataBuffer& buffer,
621 bool queue_if_blocked) {
622 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
623 SendDataParams send_params;
624
625 send_params.ordered = config_.ordered;
626 // Send as ordered if it is still going through OPEN/ACK signaling.
627 if (handshake_state_ != kHandshakeReady && !config_.ordered) {
628 send_params.ordered = true;
629 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
630 << "Sending data as ordered for unordered DataChannel "
631 "because the OPEN_ACK message has not been received.";
632 }
633
634 send_params.max_rtx_count = config_.maxRetransmits;
635 send_params.max_rtx_ms = config_.maxRetransmitTime;
636 send_params.type =
637 buffer.binary ? DataMessageType::kBinary : DataMessageType::kText;
638
639 cricket::SendDataResult send_result = cricket::SDR_SUCCESS;
640 bool success =
641 provider_->SendData(config_.id, send_params, buffer.data, &send_result);
642
643 if (success) {
644 ++messages_sent_;
645 bytes_sent_ += buffer.size();
646
647 RTC_DCHECK(buffered_amount_ >= buffer.size());
648 buffered_amount_ -= buffer.size();
649 if (observer_ && buffer.size() > 0) {
650 observer_->OnBufferedAmountChange(buffer.size());
651 }
652 return true;
653 }
654
655 if (send_result == cricket::SDR_BLOCK) {
656 if (!queue_if_blocked || QueueSendDataMessage(buffer)) {
657 return false;
658 }
659 }
660 // Close the channel if the error is not SDR_BLOCK, or if queuing the
661 // message failed.
662 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Closing the DataChannel due to a failure to send data, "
663 "send_result = "
664 << send_result;
665 CloseAbruptlyWithError(
666 RTCError(RTCErrorType::NETWORK_ERROR, "Failure to send data"));
667
668 return false;
669}
670
671bool SctpDataChannel::QueueSendDataMessage(const DataBuffer& buffer) {
672 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
673 size_t start_buffered_amount = queued_send_data_.byte_count();
674 if (start_buffered_amount + buffer.size() > kMaxQueuedSendDataBytes) {
675 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can't buffer any more data for the data channel.";
676 return false;
677 }
678 queued_send_data_.PushBack(std::make_unique<DataBuffer>(buffer));
679 return true;
680}
681
682void SctpDataChannel::SendQueuedControlMessages() {
683 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
684 PacketQueue control_packets;
685 control_packets.Swap(&queued_control_data_);
686
687 while (!control_packets.Empty()) {
688 std::unique_ptr<DataBuffer> buf = control_packets.PopFront();
689 SendControlMessage(buf->data);
690 }
691}
692
693void SctpDataChannel::QueueControlMessage(
694 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& buffer) {
695 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
696 queued_control_data_.PushBack(std::make_unique<DataBuffer>(buffer, true));
697}
698
699bool SctpDataChannel::SendControlMessage(const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& buffer) {
700 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
701 RTC_DCHECK(writable_);
702 RTC_DCHECK_GE(config_.id, 0);
703
704 bool is_open_message = handshake_state_ == kHandshakeShouldSendOpen;
705 RTC_DCHECK(!is_open_message || !config_.negotiated);
706
707 SendDataParams send_params;
708 // Send data as ordered before we receive any message from the remote peer to
709 // make sure the remote peer will not receive any data before it receives the
710 // OPEN message.
711 send_params.ordered = config_.ordered || is_open_message;
712 send_params.type = DataMessageType::kControl;
713
714 cricket::SendDataResult send_result = cricket::SDR_SUCCESS;
715 bool retval =
716 provider_->SendData(config_.id, send_params, buffer, &send_result);
717 if (retval) {
718 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Sent CONTROL message on channel " << config_.id;
719
720 if (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeShouldSendAck) {
721 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeReady;
722 } else if (handshake_state_ == kHandshakeShouldSendOpen) {
723 handshake_state_ = kHandshakeWaitingForAck;
724 }
725 } else if (send_result == cricket::SDR_BLOCK) {
726 QueueControlMessage(buffer);
727 } else {
728 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Closing the DataChannel due to a failure to send"
729 " the CONTROL message, send_result = "
730 << send_result;
731 CloseAbruptlyWithError(RTCError(RTCErrorType::NETWORK_ERROR,
732 "Failed to send a CONTROL message"));
733 }
734 return retval;
735}
736
737// static
738void SctpDataChannel::ResetInternalIdAllocatorForTesting(int new_value) {
739 g_unique_id = new_value;
740}
